node.text:
Apple’s plan to ramp up AirPods production could be delayed due to the coronavirus outbreak. Apple’s three primary AirPods manufacturers have all halted AirPods production.

Currently, all finished products are being reserved for Apple’s own retail stores and online store. This puts most of the supply constraints on other retailers. On Amazon, for instance, AirPods Pro are completely out of stock.

Even directly from Apple, AirPods Pro are still backordered by over a month.
